{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The conversation history passed to the LLM is trimmed to the most recent 10 messages when the full history exceeds the context window.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Failure boundary is prompt-construction logic (ordering/slicing), not external I/O. MOCK-MISS is low: a pure function/object test can catch off-by-one, wrong-end trimming, or role-order bugs. REAL-INFRA/LLM-DEP are not required.","test_description":"Test the history-trimming function/object directly with histories of sizes 9, 10, 11, and larger mixed-role transcripts; assert exactly the newest 10 messages are kept, in original order, and the payload passed onward contains that subset.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.84,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The generated response addresses the customer's question rather than producing a generic or off-topic reply.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real LLM output quality and variability. A mocked model would hide the real failure (generic/off-topic answers) and always pass expected text checks. This is a single model-quality step, not a multi-agent pipeline.","test_description":"Run a prompt-eval set against the production/real model with realistic user questions and history; score relevance/on-topicness using human rubric or validated evaluator, and fail if relevance falls below threshold or off-topic rate exceeds limit across repeated runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.82,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The tone re-check correctly identifies when a response is too formal for a casual-tier customer and triggers regeneration.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The key failure is tone judgment correctness ('too formal') which is model-dependent; mocking the checker can hide misclassification. Regeneration trigger wiring is integration-like, but minimum level is raised by LLM-DEP for the classification claim.","test_description":"Use a labeled set of responses (too-formal vs acceptable for casual tier) through the real tone-check path; assert flagged too-formal cases trigger a regeneration call and non-flagged cases do not, with thresholded precision/recall on tone flags.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.17,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.68,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The full exchange (user message, generated response, any regenerations) is persisted to the database with correct timestamps.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure occurs at module boundary between chat orchestration and DB persistence schema/transaction logic. Needs real DB writes/reads to catch mapping, transaction, and timestamp field issues; no real external API or LLM-quality dependency required.","test_description":"Execute chat flow against a test database, including a case with regeneration, then query persisted records and assert all expected entries exist (user message, first draft, regenerated response), linkage/session IDs are correct, and timestamps are populated and monotonic.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the tone check triggers regeneration, the second response replaces the first — the customer never sees the rejected draft.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Primary risk is orchestration/state handoff between tone-check, regeneration, and response-delivery modules. Can be caught with deterministic doubles for LLM outputs; real model quality is not required for this visibility invariant.","test_description":"Run end-to-end application service flow with controlled first/second model outputs and forced tone-trigger; assert API/service return payload contains only regenerated text, rejected draft is absent from customer-facing channel, and internal logs may still retain draft per policy.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
